    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-07-26T06:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-07-26T06:00:00-05:00" n="1359"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1359">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">881.00/7–2645: Telegram</note>
                <head>No. 1359<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Representative in the Conversations Concerning
                        Tangier</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_CJR1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Childs</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d1359fn1">Sent over the signature of <persName
                            corresp="#p_CJ1">Caffery</persName>.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-07-26T13:00:00+02:00"
                            >July 26, 1945—1 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>4505. From <persName corresp="#p_CJR1">Childs</persName>.</p>
                <p>
                    <persName corresp="#p_MJ2">Meyrier</persName> informed us today that British and
                    French were concerting together on the form of invitation to the USSR to
                    participate in the Tangier conversations to open in Paris on August 6 and that
                    it was hoped to arrive at a definite text which would (sent <gloss
                        target="#t_Dept1">Dept</gloss> as 4505; repeated Tangier as 24; Madrid as
                    281 and London as 541) be communicated to the French and British Embassies in
                    Moscow tomorrow.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
